text.section:
For purposes of this subtitle, a drug is a depressant or stimulant drug if:
it is lysergic acid diethylamide; or
it contains any quantity of:
barbituric acid or a salt of barbituric acid;
a derivative of barbituric acid that is designated as habit forming under the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act;
amphetamine or its optical isomers;
a salt of amphetamine or a salt of an optical isomer of amphetamine;
a substance that the Attorney General of the United States designates as habit-forming because of its stimulant effect on the central nervous system; or
a substance that the Attorney General of the United States designates as having a potential for abuse because of:
a depressant or stimulant effect on the central nervous system; or
a hallucinogenic effect.
